f=Cybersecurity/bastion/marketplace/cloud-posture/SKILL.md · in=Continuously monitor cloud infrastructure misconfigurations, compliance violations, security risks. Unlike traditional vulnerability scanning which focuses OS/application CVEs, CSPM focuses cloud-native risks: IAM over-permissions, exposed storage buckets, unencrypted data, missing network controls, service misconfigurations. · wu=cloud account exists (AWS, Azure, GCP)., "Is our cloud secure," "check misconfigs," "public bucket," "open port," "over-permissive IAM.", Posture scan cadence; after any infrastructure change., Compliance benchmarking against CIS, PCI DSS, NIST frameworks. · h3:AWS Security Hub=AWS Security Hub provides comprehensive view your security state AWS helps you check your environment against security industry standards best practices. **Supported Standards:** · h3:AWS Security Hub=CIS AWS Foundations Benchmark, PCI DSS, NIST SP 800-53, AWS Foundational Security Best Practices · h3:AWS Security Hub=**Key Capabilities:** · h3:AWS Security Hub=Aggregate findings AWS services (GuardDuty, Inspector, Macie, IAM Access Analyzer), Automated compliance checks, Consolidated security findings dashboard, Automated remediation AWS Config rules · h3:Azure Defender for Cloud=Azure Defender Cloud provides unified security management advanced threat protection across hybrid cloud workloads. **Key Capabilities:** · h3:Azure Defender for Cloud=Continuous assessment security configuration, Compliance scoring against CIS, PCI DSS, NIST, Azure benchmarks, Just-in-time VM access, Adaptive application controls, File integrity monitoring, Security alerts advanced threat protection · h3:Prowler (Open Source)=`# Install Prowler \· pip install prowler \· # or \· git clone https://github.com/prowler-cloud/prowler && cd prowler && pip install -r requirements.txt` · h3:Prowler (Open Source)=`# Run all checks against an AWS account \· prowler aws \·  \· # Run specific CIS checks only \· prowler aws --checks cis_1.1 cis_1.2 cis_1.3` · h3:Prowler (Open Source)=Prowler open-source command-line tool AWS, Azure, GCP security assessments, following CIS benchmarks beyond. **Installation:** **Basic Usage:** **Common Checks:** · h3:Prowler (Open Source)=S3 buckets public access, Security groups unrestricted ingress (0.0.0.0/0), IAM policies full administrative privileges (*:*), CloudTrail enabled across regions, KMS key rotation enabled, RDS instances publicly accessible · h3:ScoutSuite (Open Source)=`pip install scoutsuite` · h3:ScoutSuite (Open Source)=`# Run against AWS \· scout aws \·  \· # Run against Azure \· scout azure --cli` · h3:ScoutSuite (Open Source)=ScoutSuite multi-cloud security-auditing tool provides comprehensive view security posture AWS, Azure, GCP environments. **Installation:** **Basic Usage:** · h3:Phase 1 — Inventory=Identify cloud accounts/providers scope (per stack-profile's hosting configuration). Document services regions use. Identify any data sensitivity classifications (crown-jewel assets veil's classification). · h3:Phase 2 — Scan=Run appropriate tool cloud provider: · h3:Phase 2 — Scan=**AWS**: Prowler (CIS checks) AWS Security Hub (foundational best practices), **Azure**: Prowler (CIS checks) Azure Defender Cloud, **GCP**: Prowler (CIS checks) ScoutSuite · h3:Phase 3 — Analyze=Classify findings severity impact: · h3:Phase 3 — Analyze=**Critical**: Public storage sensitive data, internet-open databases, root/org accounts without MFA, **High**: Over-permissive IAM policies, unencrypted data rest, disabled audit logging, **Medium**: Unused security groups, non-standard configurations, **Low**: Minor deviations baseline · h3:Phase 4 — Remediate=finding: Document finding resource identifier, severity, impact. Recommend specific remediation action. Assign appropriate team operator execution. Track risk register. Re-scan after remediation confirm closure. · h2:Classic CSPM Checks (Run Scan)=**Public storage** buckets, Azure Blob containers, GCP storage buckets public access **Internet-open ports** Security groups/firewall rules 0.0.0.0/0 ingress sensitive ports (22, 3306, 3389, 5432, 27017) **Over-permissive IAM** Policies *:* effect, users/roles full admin, unused permissions **Encryption rest** Unencrypted EBS/RDS volumes, buckets without default encryption **Audit logging** CloudTrail/logging disabled misconfigured **Root/org account security** Root user without MFA, organizational guardrails (SCPs) · of=`## Cloud Posture Report: [provider/account] — [date] \· Tool used: [Prowler / ScoutSuite / Security Hub / Defender] \· Compliance benchmarks: [CIS \· PCI DSS \· NIST] \· Findings: \· Critical: [count] — [top finding]` · pr=**Check against real baselines** (CIS Benchmarks provider best practices), opinion. **The classic misconfigs breach headlines** check them scan without fail. **Prioritize exposure data sensitivity** public bucket PII misconfig dev. **Fix spec'd, applied** CSPM detects recommends; operator/ops remediates. **Findings register risks** misconfig tracked risk warden's register. **Drift finding** remediated misconfig reappears means process gap. · f=**No CSPM tooling available** manual checks against CIS Benchmark provider, prioritized classic high-blast misconfigs. Labeled "manual check tool.", **Tool access issues** (e.g., insufficient IAM permissions scan) flag finding itself; inability audit risk., **Multi-cloud** one baseline provider; shared findings across providers factored; seams between clouds flagged extra attack surface. · b:with Other Skills=**bastion's hardening-baselines** (sibling): cloud control-plane config (this skill) host/OS/endpoint config (hardening-baselines)., **bastion's network-security** (sibling): cloud SG/security group misconfigs found here; network policy designed there., **warden's risk-register**: findings register risks., **veil's data-classification**: data sensitivity exposed resources comes veil's tiers., **keyring**: over-permissive cloud IAM least-privilege failure (cloud identity seam)., **ops (Engineering)**: remediation ships through ops's deploy gate.